8 An Act relating to eminent domain; amending 27 O.S.
2021, Section 7, which relates to eminent domain for
9 light, heat, or power by electricity or gas;
clarifying applicability of provisions to certain
10 entities; prohibiting use of eminent domain for
certain facilities; requiring authorization by
11 Corporation Commission for exercise of eminent domain
by certain entities for specified purpose; and
12 declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 27 O.S. 2021, Section 7, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 7. A. Except as otherwise provided in this section,
19 any person, firm, or corporation organized under the laws of this
20 state, or authorized to do business in this state, to furnish light,
21 heat, or power by electricity or natural gas, or any other person,
22 association, or firm engaged in furnishing lights, heat, or power by
23 electricity or natural gas shall have and exercise the right of
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 352 Page 1
1 emin ent domain in the same manner and by like proceedings as
2 provided for railroad corporations by laws of this state.
3 B. The power of eminent domain shall not be used for the siting
4 or building of wind turbines energy facilities, solar energy
5 facilities, battery storage facilities, or hydrogen gas facilities
6 on private property.
7 C. Prior to seeking to exercise the right of eminent domain for
8 an electric transmission facility rated greater than three hundred
9 (300) kilovolts, any person, firm, or corporation subject to the
10 requirements of subsection A of this section shall have obtained a
11 certificate of authority from the Corporation Commission.
12 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
